other_tests.findings: There is a small right pleural effusion with associated atelectasis. Left basilar atelectasis is also noted. The liver is homogeneously hypodense with no evidence of focal lesions or biliary dilatation. There is a small amount of free fluid. Extensive peripancreatic stranding and fluid surrounding the pancreatic head and uncinate process, with no evidence of pancreatic necrosis or circumscribed collection. Eccentric thrombus within a small segment of the SMV. A 4.9 cm hypodense lesion in the lower pole of the left kidney is consistent with a cyst. Minimal thickening of the second and third portions of the duodenum, likely reactive. No evidence of retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy.
